main event: A round object was sighted while shooting morning stars by the crew of USS Durant on 20 Dec 1961.
interesting points: The object was described as being the color, size, and magnitude of Venus., The sighting lasted for seven minutes., The object was observed with the naked eye, binoculars, and a sextant., The initial sighting bearing was 295 degrees, before it disappeared at bearing 050 degrees., Conclusions were inconclusive with options including it being a balloon, aircraft, or insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: crew members from USS Durant, including a navigator
